Overall pipeline
The full system is organized as the following pipeline:
input text
  ↓
phoneme analyzer
  ↓
morpheme segmenter
  ↓
lexeme normalizer
  ↓
semantic tokenizer
  ↓
syntax / logic resolver
  ↓
DAG builder + validator
  ↓
analysis / scoring / export
Each module performs a single interpretable task and outputs a structured JSON object for the next layer.


M4. Layer by Layer Implementation:

Systematic Parse
The system should support:
	•	stable phonemic normalization,
	•	rule-based morphemic segmentation,
	•	lexeme normalization,
	•	semantic token typing,
	•	syntactic and logical relation inference,
	•	DAG construction and validation,
	•	later extension to multilingual and multimodal grounding.

4.1 Phoneme Layer
Purpose
Use the word μεγαλόδους (big teeth) as an parsing example
This layer does not perform speech recognition.
Its purpose is to convert the input into a stable phonemic signature.
Input
	•	Latin text or Ancient Greek text
	•	optionally pre-transliterated text
Operations
	•	orthographic normalization
	•	diacritic normalization
	•	grapheme/digraph to phoneme conversion
	•	syllabification
	•	phoneme feature assignment
Output
Example output schema:
{
  "surface": "μεγαλόδους",
  "normalized": "μεγαλόδους",
  "syllables": ["me", "ga", "ló", "dous"],
  "phonemes": [
    {"seg": "m", "features": {"type": "consonant", "voicing": "voiced"}},
    {"seg": "e", "features": {"type": "vowel", "height": "mid"}}
  ]
}
Resources
	•	CLTK Ancient Greek transcription
	•	CLTK Latin transcription
	•	IPA feature inventory
⸻
4.2 Morpheme Layer
Purpose
This layer performs genuine morphemic segmentation, not BPE-style frequency segmentation.
Input
	•	normalized token
	•	phoneme and syllable boundaries
Operations
	•	root matching
	•	prefix matching
	•	suffix matching
	•	inflectional ending identification
	•	candidate segmentation scoring
Output
Example schema:
{
  "token": "μεγαλόδους",
  "morphemes": [
    {"form": "μεγαλο-", "type": "prefix/combining form", "gloss": "large"},
    {"form": "οδους", "type": "root", "gloss": "tooth"}
  ]
}
Initial implementation strategy
	•	lexicon-first matching
	•	rule fallback
	•	longest valid match
	•	legality checks against morphological templates
⸻
4.3 Lexeme Layer
Purpose
This layer maps morpheme bundles to a normalized lemma / lexeme representation.
Input
	•	morpheme sequence
Operations
	•	lemma lookup
	•	variant spelling normalization
	•	terminology standardization
	•	transliteration storage
Output
Example:
{
  "lemma": "ὀδούς",
  "lexeme": "μεγαλόδους",
  "canonical_form": "megalodous",
  "pos": "NOUN"
}
Note
For compound or technical forms, the system may preserve both:
	•	the normalized lexeme,
	•	and the internal lexical source components.
⸻
4.4 Semantic Token Layer
Purpose
This layer turns the lexical unit into a word-semantics token.
Input
	•	lemma
	•	part of speech
	•	morphological information
	•	domain lexicon
Operations
Assign a semantic type and legal attachment behavior.
Output
Example:
{
  "token_id": "t1",
  "lemma": "μεγαλόδους",
  "semantic_type": "ENTITY",
  "semantic_role": "taxon_name_or_tooth_descriptor",
  "allowed_edges": ["COMPOSED_OF", "REALIZES", "GROUNDS_TO"]
}
Important principle
At this point, the token is no longer only a string.
It is now:
	•	a form,
	•	a semantic category,
	•	a set of legal graph relations,
	•	and a unit with an ambiguity profile.
⸻
4.5 Syntax / Logical Relation Layer
Purpose
This layer prevents semantic drift caused by bad attachment or scope assignment.
Input
	•	semantic tokens
	•	sentence order
	•	logical triggers
	•	relation templates
Operations
	•	head–modifier attachment
	•	argument linking
	•	negation scope
	•	comparison scope
	•	conditionals
	•	discourse relations
	•	coreference later, if needed
Output
Example:
{
  "relations": [
    {"source": "n_pred", "target": "n_subj", "type": "GOVERNS"},
    {"source": "n_neg", "target": "n_pred", "type": "SCOPES_OVER"}
  ]
}
Implementation strategy
At first:
	•	rule templates
	•	small CFG / CKY subparser
	•	operator lexicon triggers
⸻
4.6 DAG Composition Layer
Purpose
This layer merges all previous results into a typed directed acyclic graph.
Input
	•	phoneme nodes
	•	morpheme nodes
	•	lexeme nodes
	•	semantic nodes
	•	syntax / logic relations
	•	optional evidence nodes
Operations
	•	graph assembly
	•	node and edge typing
	•	acyclicity check
	•	scope closure check
	•	attachment closure check
Output
The final DAG.
Worked Example: μεγαλόδους
This section shows how the system handles the example token μεγαλόδους as an illustrative case.

Solid word check: use the word μεγαλόδους (big teeth) as an parsing example
M3a.1 Surface Form
μεγαλόδους
M3a.2 Phoneme Layer
Normalized token:
μεγαλόδους
Possible syllabification:
me | ga | ló | dous
Illustrative phonemic structure:
[
  {"seg": "m", "features": {"type": "consonant"}},
  {"seg": "e", "features": {"type": "vowel"}},
  {"seg": "g", "features": {"type": "consonant"}},
  {"seg": "a", "features": {"type": "vowel"}},
  {"seg": "l", "features": {"type": "consonant"}},
  {"seg": "ó", "features": {"type": "vowel", "stress": 1}},
  {"seg": "d", "features": {"type": "consonant"}},
  {"seg": "ou", "features": {"type": "diphthong"}},
  {"seg": "s", "features": {"type": "consonant"}}
]
M3a.3 Morpheme Layer
Illustrative segmentation:
μεγαλο- | οδους
Interpretation:
	•	μεγαλο- = large / great
	•	οδους (from ὀδούς) = tooth
Structured output:
{
  "morphemes": [
    {"form": "μεγαλο-", "type": "combining_form", "gloss": "large"},
    {"form": "οδους", "type": "root", "gloss": "tooth"}
  ]
}
M3a.4 Lexeme Layer
Possible normalized lexeme representation:
{
  "lemma": "ὀδούς",
  "lexeme": "μεγαλόδους",
  "canonical_form": "megalodous",
  "pos": "NOUN"
}
M3a.5 Semantic Token Layer
Illustrative semantic typing:
{
  "token_id": "t1",
  "lemma": "μεγαλόδους",
  "semantic_type": "ENTITY",
  "semantic_role": "large_tooth_descriptor_or_taxonomic_name",
  "allowed_edges": ["COMPOSED_OF", "REALIZES", "HAS_SEMANTIC_ROLE", "GROUNDS_TO"]
}
M3a.6 DAG-Level Interpretation
The resulting mini-graph may be represented as:
LEXEME(μεγαλόδους)
 ├── COMPOSED_OF → MORPHEME(μεγαλο-)
 ├── COMPOSED_OF → MORPHEME(οδους)
 ├── REALIZES → ENTITY(large-tooth concept / lexical entity)
 └── HAS_SEMANTIC_ROLE → SEMANTIC_ROLE(ENTITY)
If multimodal evidence is later attached:
ENTITY(large-tooth concept)
 └── GROUNDS_TO → EVIDENCE(image_patch_01)


